defined below the table. -->

| Finding ID | Surface | Scanner + rule/alert id | File:line or endpoint | Reported severity | Disposition | Status |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| {{FINDING_ID}} | {{SURFACE}} | {{SCANNER_RULE}} | {{LOCATION}} | {{SEVERITY}} | {{DISPOSITION}} | {{STATUS}} |

**Disposition vocabulary:**
- **False positive** — the scanner's pattern matched but the code is provably safe (escaped / validated / sanitized / platform-mandated construct).
- **Accepted residual (mitigated)** — a real but bounded risk accepted with a documented compensating control. Requires owner sign-off on the residual-risk line.
- **Deferred (tracked)** — a real finding to be fixed but not before this window; cross-reference the tracking item. Use sparingly — reviewers prefer fixes over deferrals.

**Status vocabulary:** `Populated` (all four parts complete + sign-off) · `DRAFT` (missing a part) · `PENDING` (awaiting the owner-run scan that produces it).

